Richard N. Haythornthwaite: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 11:22 PM ET
Multi-Utilities

Company Overview of Centrica plc



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Richard N. Haythornthwaite  Chairman, Centrica plcAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 15 different industries.See Board Relationships60495,000 GBP
Background

		Mr. Richard N. Haythornthwaite, also known as Rick, serves as the President of PSI UK Ltd. Mr. Haythornthwaite served as General Manager of BP Exploration (Alaska), Inc. He serves as President of PSA Energy. He served as a Senior Advisor of Star Capital Partners Limited. He was Managing Director of Star Capital Partners since 2006. He was a Partner of Star Capital Partners Limited from 2006 to 2008. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Invensys PLC from October 2001 ... to July 21, 2005. He served as Corporate and Commercial Director of Premier Oil plc. He served as President of BP PLC. His career started with BP PLC, where he held a variety of positions in its European and American operations from 1978 to 1995, including Chief Geologist BP France, General Manager of the Magnus Oilfield of BP Exploration and President of BP Venezuela. Mr. Haythornthwaite served as Chief Executive, Europe and Asia and then as Group Chief Executive for Blue Circle Industries plc from 1997 to 2001. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Lafarge Cement UK Ltd. since July 15, 1999 and served as its Director of Heavy Building Materials in Asia. He served as Chief Executive Officer of Heavy Building Materials Asia and Europe, since January 1, 1998. His career has spanned extensive experience in organizational and cultural change leadership, cost reduction programs, results-driven performance initiatives and executing and negotiating acquisitions and divestments worldwide. He has over twenty years of international industry experience covering a broad mix of strategic and operational roles. He served as President of Almeida Theatre. Mr. Haythornthwaite serves as Chairman of the Corporate Advisory Group of the Tate Gallery. He serves as the Chairman of the Board at ARC International SA. He serves as Chairman of the Board of SAlmeida Theatre. He serves as Chairman of the Centre for Creative Communities. He has been Non-Executive Chairman of MasterCard Incorporated since September 14, 2006. He has been the Chairman of the Board of Centrica Energy Operations Limited since January 01, 2014 and is its Non-Executive Director since October 14, 2013. He serves as the Chairman of MasterCard Worldwide, Inc. He serves as Chairman at Southbank Centre Board and MasterCard International Inc and has been its Director since May 2006. He has been the Chairman at Centrica plc since January 1, 2014. He serves as Chair of the World Wide Web Foundation. He has been Director of MasterCard Worldwide and MasterCard Incorporated since May 2006. He has been a Non-Executive Director of Centrica plc since October 14, 2013. He serves as a Director at CAST. He serves as a Director of the National Museum of Science and Industry. He serves as Member of Advisory Board of Almeida Theatre. Mr. Haythornthwaite served as a Non-Executive Director at Network Rail Limited from March 23, 2009 to July 19, 2012. He served as Chairman of Network Rail Limited from July 21, 2009 to July 19, 2012. He served as Chairman of Retail Portfolio at Land Securities Group plc. Mr. Haythornthwaite served as the Chairman of Network Rail Infrastructure Limited from March 23, 2009 to July 19, 2012 and served as its Director from March 2009 to July 19, 2012. He served as a Non-Executive Director of Imperial Chemical Industries PLC since February 20, 2001. He served as a Non-Executive Director of Lafarge S.A from 2001 to July 1, 2003. He served as Non-Executive Director of Land Securities Group plc from April 1, 2008 to February 5, 2009. He served as an Executive Director of Lafarge Cement UK since October 1, 1997. He served as a Non-Executive Director of Vesuvius plc from 1999 to April 24, 2003. He served as a Director of Premier Oil PLC since 1995, where he was responsible for corporate and commercial affairs. He served as a Director of Invensys PLC from July 2001 to July 21, 2005. He serves as Trustee of the UK National Museum of Science and Industry. He serves as the Chairman of the Risk and Regulatory Advisory Council at South Bank Centre. He served as a Director of the British Council. Mr. Haythornthwaite is a graduate of Queens College, Oxford, with a Degree in Geology and a Sloan Fellow of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.Read Full Background




